# Docker build context exclusions.
#
# The bundled image needs the editor source + the Go backend; nothing
# else. Everything large or generated stays out of the build context
# so `docker build` doesn't ship 2 GB of node_modules / build output /
# fixtures to the daemon.

# Top-level build artifacts + IDE
.git/
.idea/
*.iml
.DS_Store

# Per-language artifacts
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/out/
**/target/
**/.next/

# Test outputs
**/playwright-report/
**/test-results/
**/screenshots/

# Local-only env / secrets
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*

# Reference docs / large fixtures we don't ship.
# Use `/<path>` so they match only at the build-context root and we
# don't accidentally exclude (e.g.) docx-editor/assets/ from the
# editor build.
/docx-editor/reference/
/docx-editor/e2e/fixtures/
/docx-editor/playwright-report/
/docx-editor/test-results/
/docx-editor/screenshots/
/docx-editor/roundtrip-audit-report.md
/docs/
/assets/

# Editor doesn't need this — the gateway builds from backend/ only
**/*.log
